<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "1C">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B1306004" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Electric Throttle Body Assembly On-Vehicle Inspection
</title>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
Never touch throttle valve with finger while ignition is “ON” and accelerator pedal is depressed. Otherwise, the finger may be pinched between throttle valve and throttle body housing.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not disassemble electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not drop or expose electric throttle body assembly to excessive shock. Electric throttle body assembly exposed to excessive shock should be replaced.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Keep the throttle body housing and/or throttle valve free of dust, metallic particles or other foreign materials. Contamination by these materials may cause throttle body assembly to break down.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not apply excessive forces to throttle valve when checking operation of throttle valve or performance of TP sensor; otherwise plastic gears in throttle valve actuator will be damaged.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
After replacing electric throttle body assembly, calibration of throttle valve position is required. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1306004001" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Valve Visual Check
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that there is no foreign materials caught between throttle valve and throttle body housing. If foreign materials are present, remove throttle body and clean its inside thoroughly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1306004002" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Valve Operation Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check throttle valve operation as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace throttle body. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check that throttle valve (1) moves smoothly to both fully closed position and fully open position when pressed manually.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7N301132006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.110mm" ver = "01" gw = "170" gh = "126"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check throttle valve returns to default position when finger pressure on throttle valve is released at both fully closed position and fully open position.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Throttle valve default position “a”:
</title>
<ptxt>
7&#176; from fully closed position (1)
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A131002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.759mm" ver = "04" gw = "144" gh = "108"/>
</figure>
</spec>
</s2>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1306004003" page = "2">
<title>
Electric Throttle Body System Operation Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check electric throttle body system as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, go to Step 4).
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Depress accelerator pedal gradually and check that throttle valve moves smoothly until it opens fully.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Release accelerator pedal and check that throttle valve moves back to applicable position.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Throttle valve opening angle “a”:
</title>
<ptxt>
3 to 15&#176; from completely closed position (1)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A131002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.759mm" ver = "04" gw = "144" gh = "108"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check the following points.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If check results are satisfactory, replace electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Wire harness and connections
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
APP sensor 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
TP sensor:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Refer to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70B1306004005">Throttle Position (TP) Sensor Performance Check</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Throttle motor:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Refer to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70B1306004004">Throttle Motor Check</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1306004004" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Motor Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector from electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Measure resistance between terminal “1” and terminal “2” of electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace electric throttle body assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Throttle motor resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
0.3 to 100 &#937; at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7N301132008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "27.180mm" ver = "02" gw = "110" gh = "61"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1306004005" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Position (TP) Sensor Performance Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector from electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check output voltage of TP sensor main and sub signals as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace electric throttle body. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Arrange 3 new 1.5 V batteries (1) in series, and check that total voltage is 4.5 to 5.0 V.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Connect voltmeter (2) and batteries to TP sensor as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A131020.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "91.672mm" ver = "01" gw = "152" gh = "243"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.311in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.489in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.311in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.353in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
TP sensor (main)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
TP sensor (sub)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage varies depending on throttle opening angle as following graph while throttle valve is opened and closed manually.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A131001.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.784mm" ver = "03" gw = "239" gh = "125"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.259in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.182in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[a]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
TP sensor (main) voltage
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[b]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
TP sensor (sub) voltage
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[c]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
TP sensor output voltage
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[d]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Throttle valve opening
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[e]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Position where throttle valve is open by 7&#176; from fully closed position (default position)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
